            "answer_text": "Atomic number = 12 (magnesium, Mg) Number of electrons in the atom = 12 The element's electronic configuration is 1s2 2s2 2p6 3s2 ( or 2,8,2). The last 2 electrons are in the s orbital of the shell having the principal quantum number 3. Since it is an s-block element having 2 electrons in the outermost shell, it will belong to group 2. And, since the outermost shell's principal quantum number is 3, the element is in period 3. ",
